# Stack

Next.js App Router · TypeScript strict · Supabase (Auth, Postgres, Storage, Realtime) · Server Actions · Zod · Tailwind / shadcn/ui

## Mutation Flow

```
Client → Server Action → Zod → Auth/Permission → Service → Supabase → Audit Log → revalidatePath/Tag
```

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Does | Does NOT |
|-------|------|----------|
| Page / Component | Render UI, call actions | Business logic, direct DB writes |
| Server Action | Validate, auth, orchestrate | Complex business rules |
| Service | Workflows, scoring, audit | UI concerns |
| Queries | Read-only Supabase access | Mutations |

## Environment

Browser-safe: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`

Server-only: `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `DATABASE_URL`, all other secrets
